	joy
	|--axes
	|  |--left_toggle_x
	|  |--left_toggle_y
	|  |--left_trigger
	|  |--right_toggle_x
	|  |--right_toggle_y
	|  |--right_trigger
	|--buttons
	   |
	   v
	   ...

	** the linuxjoy program reads from a sensor
	** message with joystick information and outputs
	** a velocity message.

	** commands are mapped to axes and buttons via
	** the ros parameters

	** COMPILE
	** this software cannot run without ros, use catkin_make
	** in the top level project directory

	** COMMANDS (default)
	** translate_x -> left_joy_axis_y
	** translate_y -> none
	** translate_z -> none
	** rol -> none
	** ptc -> none
	** yaw -> right_joy_axis_x

	** NAMESPACE (default)
	** /cmd_vel
